chunk_content: Potential scenarios for reporting a child in this category include: o Final outcome not yet confirmed for HIV-exposed infants o Not yet assessed: Child enrolled in program, but not yet assessed for HIV risk. 121 o Refuse HIV assessment: Caregiver has been approached but did not agree to let the IP conduct a risk assessment on the child in the reporting period. o At risk for HIV: Child has been assessed and is at risk for HIV, but caregiver has not yet T E taken child to be tested (including if they have refused testing referral or if they have S accepted the referral but not yet completed the test). T I o HIV referral completed: OVC has completed HIV test, but result is not available OR N caregiver doesn’t report results to IP in the reporting period. G o Refuse report: Caregiver has been approached by IP but has not yet agreed to disclose whether the child has been tested and his/her current HIV status in the reporting period.
